		<description><![CDATA[Nice stuff! And it&#039;s VERY useful for performing bassists, too! It&#039;s not just for the beginners!!
I&#039;m kinda hooked way too much on a &quot;you gotta finger every note&quot; mentality and sometimes (especially when I&#039;m improvising) throwing in more hammer-ons can be a life-saver! ^_^ (ok, well, performance-saver, let&#039;s say... :P )
You know what? To &quot;space out&quot; the hammer-ons and shifts more evenly, I&#039;ve found myself that prefer going like this (referring to your Cmaj scale exercise):
C-D
E-F-G-shift-A
B-C-D
E-F-G-shift-A]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Nice stuff! And it&#8217;s VERY useful for performing bassists, too! It&#8217;s not just for the beginners!!<br />
I&#8217;m kinda hooked way too much on a &#8220;you gotta finger every note&#8221; mentality and sometimes (especially when I&#8217;m improvising) throwing in more hammer-ons can be a life-saver! ^_^ (ok, well, performance-saver, let&#8217;s say&#8230; :P )<br />
You know what? To &#8220;space out&#8221; the hammer-ons and shifts more evenly, I&#8217;ve found myself that prefer going like this (referring to your Cmaj scale exercise):<br />
C-D<br />
E-F-G-shift-A<br />
B-C-D<br />
E-F-G-shift-A</p>
]]></content:encoded>
