		<description><![CDATA[Thanks Scott for such an amazing lesson.  I just has a huge &quot;Ah-Ha&quot; moment!  I never used hammer-ons effectively in the past.  I used them more as ghost notes.  The light went on when you mentioned that the hammer-on note should sound as if is a plucked note.  And, as you mentioned, done correctly, it will improve my speed since I&#039;m not actually plucking every single note.  Again, thanks a million!]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Thanks Scott for such an amazing lesson.  I just has a huge &#8220;Ah-Ha&#8221; moment!  I never used hammer-ons effectively in the past.  I used them more as ghost notes.  The light went on when you mentioned that the hammer-on note should sound as if is a plucked note.  And, as you mentioned, done correctly, it will improve my speed since I&#8217;m not actually plucking every single note.  Again, thanks a million!</p>
